==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mameluke
<hw>Mam"e*luke</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>mamelouk</ets>, cf. Sp. <ets>mameluco</ets>, It.
<ets>mammalucco</ets>; all fr. Ar. <ets>maml⟦umac⟧k</ets> a purchased
slave or captive; lit., possessed or in one's power, p. p. of
<ets>malaka</ets> to possesses.]</ety> <def>One of a body of mounted
soldiers recruited from slaves converted to Muslimism, who, during
several centuries, had more or less control of the government of Egypt,
until exterminated or dispersed by <person>Mehemet Ali</person> in
1811.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mamillated</ent>⟦br⟧
